{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"2961bd88-c930-4506-bcca-f9d40cc278bf","agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are the SIMILARITY AUDITOR for a clean-room process (read /home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/PROTOCOL.md; prior audits passed round-1 of both clusters). Audit ONLY the round-2 additions of two clean crates against the GPL Haskell originals, applying abstraction-filtration (identical output strings/behavior/API-doc names are NOT violations; flag internal decomposition mirroring the Haskell where alternatives exist, non-observable internal names matching Haskell internals, echoed comments, or algorithmic expression matching where behavior admits materially different implementations).\n\nCLUSTER 1 (graph): round-2 delta = abbreviation SELECTION policy in /home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/graphdot/workspace/graph-clean/src/abbrev.rs (abbrev::select, MIN_ABBREV_LEN=10, MIN_ABBREV_OCC=2, tuple exclusion, bottom-up ordering) and term.rs additions (render_len/is_tuple), plus tests/abbrev_tests.rs additions. Haskell original: the term-judging/selection logic in the tamarin-prover submodule — find it under /home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/tamarin-prover/lib/theory/src/Theory/Constraint/System/ (Abbreviation module; judgeTerm/soft-limit/weight machinery). Key question: does the clean selection rule reproduce the Haskell's EXPRESSION (constants, weight formula, decomposition) or only its observable BEHAVIOR? Note the clean side derived length-10/occ-2 empirically from 97,538 corpus examples and live boundary probes (documented in QUERIES.log/BEHAVIOR.md §5c) — verify the Haskell's actual mechanism differs or matches, and whether the clean code mirrors anything non-observable.\n\nCLUSTER 2 (web): round-2 delta = examples/corpus_html.rs bulk harness, tests/fixtures/html_sample.ndjson + the new generality test, and any template/model edits made this round in /home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/ (git is not available there; identify round-2 changes from workspace/REPORT2.md). Haskell originals: /home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/tamarin-prover/src/Web/{Theory,Hamlet,Types,Handler}.hs.\n\nAppend findings to the respective AUDIT.md files under \"## Round 2 incremental audit\". Return a short plain-text verdict per cluster (\"graph: pass|redo; web: pass|redo\") with one-paragraph justifications and finding counts. Do not modify any other files."},"uuid":"16718671-1c83-40f5-974d-c81a4011f053","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:31:44.938Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
