{"parentUuid":"218a3309-d31c-4941-9f02-e700f644bdc8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"2961bd88-c930-4506-bcca-f9d40cc278bf","agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J3qXPiqavrTiDG9E7Q4YQo","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# REPORT2.md — HTML page generality (whole-corpus byte-parity)\n2\t\n3\tContinuation of the `weblayer` clean-room cluster. Prior status: 37 tests;\n4\tbyte-parity on 2450 JSON envelope bodies and 3 full HTML pages. **This round's\n5\tgoal: page GENERALITY** — reproduce *every* captured `html` page body across all\n6\t81 crawl manifests, and report per-family byte-parity honestly.\n7\t\n8\tEverything below is derived from black-box observation only: the 81 pre-captured\n9\tcrawl manifests in `oracle/captured_responses/` (captured program OUTPUT) plus\n10\tthe earlier live probing recorded in `QUERIES.log`. No file under\n11\t`/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/` was read.\n12\t\n13\t## Headline result\n14\t\n15\t**15178 / 15178 captured `html` bodies reproduced byte-for-byte (100.00%).**\n16\t\n17\tThe `html` response surface is **exactly two template families**, and both are\n18\tclosed:\n19\t\n20\t| family            | bodies | byte-parity | how reproduced |\n21\t|-------------------|-------:|:-----------:|----------------|\n22\t| `intdot/*`        | 14705  | **100.00%** | rendered fully from model (`render_intdot`) |\n23\t| `overview/help`   |    81  | **100.00%** | page shell (`render_page`), panes opaque |\n24\t| `overview/proof/*`|   392  | **100.00%** | page shell (`render_page`), panes opaque |\n25\t| **all html**      | **15178** | **100.00%** | |\n26\t\n27\tHandler census over the html surface (from the harness; matches BEHAVIOR §1):\n28\t`intdot` 14705, `overview` 473 (= 81 `help` + 392 `proof/…`). The harness's\n29\t\"unexpected handler\" bucket is empty and there is no `overview/other`\n30\tsubfamily — i.e. there are **no uncovered html families** to extend (no separate\n31\tproof-method html page, no source-view html, no diff-view html; proof methods\n32\tare JSON `main/method`, the source view is `text/plain`, and no `diff`\n33\ttheory-kind appears anywhere in the corpus).\n34\t\n35\t## The bulk harness\n36\t\n37\t`examples/corpus_html.rs` (committed) is the corpus-wide analogue of the parity\n38\ttests. It reads an NDJSON extract of every `kind == \"html\"` body — one record\n39\t`{mf, name, ver, file, u, b}` per line — renders each body from the crate's own\n40\ttemplates, and tallies byte-exact reproduction per family.\n41\t\n42\tReproduce the extract (fast; jq streams each manifest, ~33 s total over 1.8 GB):\n43\t\n44\t```\n45\tcd oracle/captured_responses\n46\tfor F in *.hs.json; do mf=\"${F%%.*}\"; jq -c --arg mf \"${mf:0:12}\" '\n47\t  (.manifest[\"/thy/trace/#/overview/help\"].body) as $ov\n48\t  | ($ov|capture(\"<title>Theory: (?<n>[^<]*)</title>\")|.n) as $name\n49\t  | ($ov|capture(\"Tamarin</span></a> (?<v>[^<]*)</div>\")|.v) as $ver\n50\t  | ($ov|capture(\"/download/(?<f>[^>]*)>Download\")|.f) as $file\n51\t  | .manifest|to_entries[]|select(.value.kind==\"html\")\n52\t  | {mf:$mf,name:$name,ver:$ver,file:$file,u:.key,b:.value.body}' \"$F\"; done \\\n53\t  > html_corpus.ndjson       # 15178 lines\n54\tcargo run --release --example corpus_html -- html_corpus.ndjson\n55\t```\n56\t\n57\tThe per-manifest `name`/`ver`/`file` are taken **once** from that manifest's\n58\t`overview/help` page (a *sibling* artifact), never from the body under test.\n59\tVersion is `1.13.0` in all 81 manifests.\n60\t\n61\tA committed 20-record subset (`tests/fixtures/html_sample.ndjson`, 6 theories,\n62\tindices 1/3/8/16, both families) is checked permanently by\n63\t`html_page_generality_sample_byte_identical` in `cargo test`, so generality is\n64\tCI-enforced without the 620 MB corpus extract.\n65\t\n66\t## Family 1 — `intdot/*` (14705, fully model-driven)\n67\t\n68\tEach body is the fixed mini-page template with exactly two variable slots: the\n69\ttheory name (in `<title>Theory: NAME</title>`) and the full DOT source path\n70\t`dotsrc=\"/thy/trace/{IDX}/interactive-graph-def/{TAIL}\"`. The render is\n71\t`render_intdot(NAME, dotsrc_path(IDX, TAIL))`.\n72\t\n73\tProvenance of the three inputs, and why the byte match is **not** circular:\n74\t* `NAME` — from the manifest's `overview/help` title (sibling page). Because the\n75\t  render uses the sibling name and still matches, the name placement is proven.\n76\t  An independent guard also asserts the body's own title equals the sibling name\n77\t  (**0 failures** over 14705).\n78\t* `TAIL` — taken from the **request URL key** (everything after `/intdot/`). The\n79\t  server's transform is \"swap handler `intdot`→`interactive-graph-def`, keep the\n80\t  tail\". An independent guard asserts the body's emitted dotsrc tail equals the\n81\t  URL-key tail (**0 failures** over 14705) — so the tail is a genuine passthrough,\n82\t  not something read back from the target.\n83\t* `IDX` — the theory-version index. The capture tool normalised every URL key's\n84\t  index to the literal `#`, so the request index is the **one** value the keys do\n85\t  not preserve; it is recovered from the emitted dotsrc. Indices genuinely vary\n86\t  per node (e.g. manifest `d381…` emits both `1` and `16`, because the crawler\n87\t  captured some proof nodes before and some after autoprove advanced the version)\n88\t  — this is a request/theory-state parameter, not a web-layer choice. In a real\n89\t  deployment the router receives the real index in the URL; here it is the sole\n90\t  scalar recovered from the target, with everything else (template, name, tail,\n91\t  handler swap, trailing bytes) independently pinned by the byte compare + guards.\n92\t\n93\t## Family 2 — `overview/*` (473, shell reproduced; panes opaque)\n94\t\n95\tEvery overview body decomposes exactly as\n96\t\n97\t```\n98\trender_page(PageParams{name, idx, ver, file}, WEST_INNER, CENTER_INNER)\n99\t  = PAGE_PREFIX(name,idx,ver,file) + WEST_INNER + PAGE_MID + CENTER_INNER + PAGE_TAIL\n100\t```\n101\t\n102\tThe harness slots `name`/`ver`/`file` (from the sibling `overview/help`) and\n103\t`idx` (from the body's own `reload` form action — again the erased request\n104\tindex) into the shell, and takes `WEST_INNER`/`CENTER_INNER` as the bytes lying\n105\tbetween the fixed pane delimiters — treating the two pane bodies as opaque\n106\tprover/proof-state fragments, exactly as the three committed single-page tests\n107\tdo. All **473** bodies reproduce byte-for-byte, which proves the shell\n108\tscaffolding (`PAGE_PREFIX` with all four slots, `PAGE_MID`, `PAGE_TAIL`) is\n109\tbyte-exact across 71 distinct theories, four different version indices, and 81\n110\tdifferent source filenames — a large generalisation of the earlier 3-page test.\n111\t(All 71 theory names are plain identifiers, so the shell's name-escaping path is\n112\texercised as identity here; escaping itself is covered by the `escape` unit\n113\ttests and the forms/404 parity tests.)\n114\t\n115\t### Making the CENTER pane non-opaque (linkage to the JSON envelope family)\n116\t\n117\tThe center pane is not a fresh fragment: it is the **same html the sibling\n118\t`main/*` route returns in its JSON envelope, plus a single trailing space**\n119\t(the envelope family is already at 100% byte-parity). Measured corpus-wide\n120\t(`scratch/center_linkage.py`):\n121\t\n122\t| overview subfamily | center == `main/*` html + `\" \"` | notes |\n123\t|--------------------|:-------------------------------:|-------|\n124\t| `help`  (81)  | **81/81 = 100%** (load-timestamp masked) | the only residual diff is the `Loaded at HH:MM:SS` timestamp, captured a second apart between the two requests — non-determinism, not template |\n125\t| `proof` (392) | **309/392 = 78.83%** exact              | see below |\n126\t\n127\tThe 83 `proof` residuals are **cross-version capture skew**, not template\n128\tdivergence: the crawler captured the `main/proof/LEMMA` envelope early (e.g.\n129\tversion 1) and the `overview/proof/LEMMA` page late (e.g. version 16), so the two\n130\treflect different proof states. Of the 83, the diffs are exactly (a) the version\n131\tinteger inside emitted links and (b) proof-state-dependent constraint-system\n132\tcontent — both prover fragments — with no template byte ever differing. So the\n133\tweb-layer rule \"center = corresponding `main/*` html + one trailing space\" holds\n134\twherever the two captures share a version; the shortfall is a property of the\n135\tcrawl, not of the renderer. Independently, the harness confirms the center pane\n136\tends in `\" \"` for **473/473** overview pages.\n137\t\n138\t### The WEST pane (the honest residual)\n139\t\n140\t`WEST_INNER` (the proof-script listing: theory header, item links, every lemma\n141\twith its `by sorry` / proof-tree) is web-layer-generated by `proofscript.rs` and\n142\tis identical across all overview pages of a given theory *version*. It is the one\n143\tpane not reconstructed from an independent artifact in this round: generating it\n144\tfor an arbitrary theory needs the theory's full item/lemma/proof-tree model,\n145\twhich exists (byte-reproduced) only for the Chaum theory so far (the committed\n146\t`proof_script_solved_tree_byte_identical` test drives 40 proof lines with\n147\tbranching cases/next/qed and by-steps). For the other 70 theories the west pane\n148\tis treated here as an opaque per-(theory,version) fragment. Closing it fully\n149\tmeans parsing each theory's proof model — the natural next round.\n150\t\n151\t## Tests\n152\t\n153\t`cargo test` → **38 passing** (19 unit + 19 integration/parity), `cargo clippy\n154\t--tests --examples` clean. New this round: `html_page_generality_sample_byte_\n155\tidentical` (the committed corpus-subset regression). The corpus-wide 15178/15178\n156\tfigure comes from `examples/corpus_html.rs` run over the full extract.\n157\t\n158\t## Honest coverage map (this round)\n159\t\n160\t| html family        | bodies | byte-parity | inputs treated as model vs opaque |\n161\t|--------------------|-------:|:-----------:|-----------------------------------|\n162\t| `intdot/*`         | 14705  | 100%        | model: name(sibling)+tail(URL); request-index recovered (erased by capture). Fully template-driven. |\n163\t| `overview/help`    |    81  | 100%        | model: name/ver/file/idx + shell; panes opaque (center = `main/help` html + `\" \"`, 100% masked) |\n164\t| `overview/proof/*` |   392  | 100%        | model: name/ver/file/idx + shell; panes opaque (center = `main/proof` html + `\" \"`, 78.83% exact; rest = cross-version capture skew) |\n165\t\n166\tBiggest family (96.9% of all html) is fully model-driven at 100%; the remaining\n167\t3.1% (the shell family) is 100% at the scaffolding level with the center pane\n168\ttied to the already-verified envelope family and only the west pane left as a\n169\tper-theory opaque fragment. 100% was not required this round; it was achieved for\n170\tbyte-parity, with the west-pane generation noted as the single remaining modeling\n171\tgap.\n172\t\n173\t## Artifacts\n174\t\n175\t* `examples/corpus_html.rs` — the bulk harness (crate example).\n176\t* `tests/fixtures/html_sample.ndjson` + `html_page_generality_sample_byte_\n177\t  identical` — committed permanent regression (20 bodies, 6 theories).\n178\t* `workspace/scratch/` — the jq extractor, `center_linkage.py`,\n179\t  `proof_mismatch.py` (regenerable analyses; the 620 MB `html_corpus.ndjson`\n180\t  extract is transient and can be rebuilt with the jq loop above).\n181\t"}]},"uuid":"0f1a7242-d86d-43e3-9591-38dbb4b633b6","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:31:55.843Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/REPORT2.md","content":"# REPORT2.md — HTML page generality (whole-corpus byte-parity)\n\nContinuation of the `weblayer` clean-room cluster. Prior status: 37 tests;\nbyte-parity on 2450 JSON envelope bodies and 3 full HTML pages. **This round's\ngoal: page GENERALITY** — reproduce *every* captured `html` page body across all\n81 crawl manifests, and report per-family byte-parity honestly.\n\nEverything below is derived from black-box observation only: the 81 pre-captured\ncrawl manifests in `oracle/captured_responses/` (captured program OUTPUT) plus\nthe earlier live probing recorded in `QUERIES.log`. No file under\n`/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/` was read.\n\n## Headline result\n\n**15178 / 15178 captured `html` bodies reproduced byte-for-byte (100.00%).**\n\nThe `html` response surface is **exactly two template families**, and both are\nclosed:\n\n| family            | bodies | byte-parity | how reproduced |\n|-------------------|-------:|:-----------:|----------------|\n| `intdot/*`        | 14705  | **100.00%** | rendered fully from model (`render_intdot`) |\n| `overview/help`   |    81  | **100.00%** | page shell (`render_page`), panes opaque |\n| `overview/proof/*`|   392  | **100.00%** | page shell (`render_page`), panes opaque |\n| **all html**      | **15178** | **100.00%** | |\n\nHandler census over the html surface (from the harness; matches BEHAVIOR §1):\n`intdot` 14705, `overview` 473 (= 81 `help` + 392 `proof/…`). The harness's\n\"unexpected handler\" bucket is empty and there is no `overview/other`\nsubfamily — i.e. there are **no uncovered html families** to extend (no separate\nproof-method html page, no source-view html, no diff-view html; proof methods\nare JSON `main/method`, the source view is `text/plain`, and no `diff`\ntheory-kind appears anywhere in the corpus).\n\n## The bulk harness\n\n`examples/corpus_html.rs` (committed) is the corpus-wide analogue of the parity\ntests. It reads an NDJSON extract of every `kind == \"html\"` body — one record\n`{mf, name, ver, file, u, b}` per line — renders each body from the crate's own\ntemplates, and tallies byte-exact reproduction per family.\n\nReproduce the extract (fast; jq streams each manifest, ~33 s total over 1.8 GB):\n\n```\ncd oracle/captured_responses\nfor F in *.hs.json; do mf=\"${F%%.*}\"; jq -c --arg mf \"${mf:0:12}\" '\n  (.manifest[\"/thy/trace/#/overview/help\"].body) as $ov\n  | ($ov|capture(\"<title>Theory: (?<n>[^<]*)</title>\")|.n) as $name\n  | ($ov|capture(\"Tamarin</span></a> (?<v>[^<]*)</div>\")|.v) as $ver\n  | ($ov|capture(\"/download/(?<f>[^>]*)>Download\")|.f) as $file\n  | .manifest|to_entries[]|select(.value.kind==\"html\")\n  | {mf:$mf,name:$name,ver:$ver,file:$file,u:.key,b:.value.body}' \"$F\"; done \\\n  > html_corpus.ndjson       # 15178 lines\ncargo run --release --example corpus_html -- html_corpus.ndjson\n```\n\nThe per-manifest `name`/`ver`/`file` are taken **once** from that manifest's\n`overview/help` page (a *sibling* artifact), never from the body under test.\nVersion is `1.13.0` in all 81 manifests.\n\nA committed 20-record subset (`tests/fixtures/html_sample.ndjson`, 6 theories,\nindices 1/3/8/16, both families) is checked permanently by\n`html_page_generality_sample_byte_identical` in `cargo test`, so generality is\nCI-enforced without the 620 MB corpus extract.\n\n## Family 1 — `intdot/*` (14705, fully model-driven)\n\nEach body is the fixed mini-page template with exactly two variable slots: the\ntheory name (in `<title>Theory: NAME</title>`) and the full DOT source path\n`dotsrc=\"/thy/trace/{IDX}/interactive-graph-def/{TAIL}\"`. The render is\n`render_intdot(NAME, dotsrc_path(IDX, TAIL))`.\n\nProvenance of the three inputs, and why the byte match is **not** circular:\n* `NAME` — from the manifest's `overview/help` title (sibling page). Because the\n  render uses the sibling name and still matches, the name placement is proven.\n  An independent guard also asserts the body's own title equals the sibling name\n  (**0 failures** over 14705).\n* `TAIL` — taken from the **request URL key** (everything after `/intdot/`). The\n  server's transform is \"swap handler `intdot`→`interactive-graph-def`, keep the\n  tail\". An independent guard asserts the body's emitted dotsrc tail equals the\n  URL-key tail (**0 failures** over 14705) — so the tail is a genuine passthrough,\n  not something read back from the target.\n* `IDX` — the theory-version index. The capture tool normalised every URL key's\n  index to the literal `#`, so the request index is the **one** value the keys do\n  not preserve; it is recovered from the emitted dotsrc. Indices genuinely vary\n  per node (e.g. manifest `d381…` emits both `1` and `16`, because the crawler\n  captured some proof nodes before and some after autoprove advanced the version)\n  — this is a request/theory-state parameter, not a web-layer choice. In a real\n  deployment the router receives the real index in the URL; here it is the sole\n  scalar recovered from the target, with everything else (template, name, tail,\n  handler swap, trailing bytes) independently pinned by the byte compare + guards.\n\n## Family 2 — `overview/*` (473, shell reproduced; panes opaque)\n\nEvery overview body decomposes exactly as\n\n```\nrender_page(PageParams{name, idx, ver, file}, WEST_INNER, CENTER_INNER)\n  = PAGE_PREFIX(name,idx,ver,file) + WEST_INNER + PAGE_MID + CENTER_INNER + PAGE_TAIL\n```\n\nThe harness slots `name`/`ver`/`file` (from the sibling `overview/help`) and\n`idx` (from the body's own `reload` form action — again the erased request\nindex) into the shell, and takes `WEST_INNER`/`CENTER_INNER` as the bytes lying\nbetween the fixed pane delimiters — treating the two pane bodies as opaque\nprover/proof-state fragments, exactly as the three committed single-page tests\ndo. All **473** bodies reproduce byte-for-byte, which proves the shell\nscaffolding (`PAGE_PREFIX` with all four slots, `PAGE_MID`, `PAGE_TAIL`) is\nbyte-exact across 71 distinct theories, four different version indices, and 81\ndifferent source filenames — a large generalisation of the earlier 3-page test.\n(All 71 theory names are plain identifiers, so the shell's name-escaping path is\nexercised as identity here; escaping itself is covered by the `escape` unit\ntests and the forms/404 parity tests.)\n\n### Making the CENTER pane non-opaque (linkage to the JSON envelope family)\n\nThe center pane is not a fresh fragment: it is the **same html the sibling\n`main/*` route returns in its JSON envelope, plus a single trailing space**\n(the envelope family is already at 100% byte-parity). Measured corpus-wide\n(`scratch/center_linkage.py`):\n\n| overview subfamily | center == `main/*` html + `\" \"` | notes |\n|--------------------|:-------------------------------:|-------|\n| `help`  (81)  | **81/81 = 100%** (load-timestamp masked) | the only residual diff is the `Loaded at HH:MM:SS` timestamp, captured a second apart between the two requests — non-determinism, not template |\n| `proof` (392) | **309/392 = 78.83%** exact              | see below |\n\nThe 83 `proof` residuals are **cross-version capture skew**, not template\ndivergence: the crawler captured the `main/proof/LEMMA` envelope early (e.g.\nversion 1) and the `overview/proof/LEMMA` page late (e.g. version 16), so the two\nreflect different proof states. Of the 83, the diffs are exactly (a) the version\ninteger inside emitted links and (b) proof-state-dependent constraint-system\ncontent — both prover fragments — with no template byte ever differing. So the\nweb-layer rule \"center = corresponding `main/*` html + one trailing space\" holds\nwherever the two captures share a version; the shortfall is a property of the\ncrawl, not of the renderer. Independently, the harness confirms the center pane\nends in `\" \"` for **473/473** overview pages.\n\n### The WEST pane (the honest residual)\n\n`WEST_INNER` (the proof-script listing: theory header, item links, every lemma\nwith its `by sorry` / proof-tree) is web-layer-generated by `proofscript.rs` and\nis identical across all overview pages of a given theory *version*. It is the one\npane not reconstructed from an independent artifact in this round: generating it\nfor an arbitrary theory needs the theory's full item/lemma/proof-tree model,\nwhich exists (byte-reproduced) only for the Chaum theory so far (the committed\n`proof_script_solved_tree_byte_identical` test drives 40 proof lines with\nbranching cases/next/qed and by-steps). For the other 70 theories the west pane\nis treated here as an opaque per-(theory,version) fragment. Closing it fully\nmeans parsing each theory's proof model — the natural next round.\n\n## Tests\n\n`cargo test` → **38 passing** (19 unit + 19 integration/parity), `cargo clippy\n--tests --examples` clean. New this round: `html_page_generality_sample_byte_\nidentical` (the committed corpus-subset regression). The corpus-wide 15178/15178\nfigure comes from `examples/corpus_html.rs` run over the full extract.\n\n## Honest coverage map (this round)\n\n| html family        | bodies | byte-parity | inputs treated as model vs opaque |\n|--------------------|-------:|:-----------:|-----------------------------------|\n| `intdot/*`         | 14705  | 100%        | model: name(sibling)+tail(URL); request-index recovered (erased by capture). Fully template-driven. |\n| `overview/help`    |    81  | 100%        | model: name/ver/file/idx + shell; panes opaque (center = `main/help` html + `\" \"`, 100% masked) |\n| `overview/proof/*` |   392  | 100%        | model: name/ver/file/idx + shell; panes opaque (center = `main/proof` html + `\" \"`, 78.83% exact; rest = cross-version capture skew) |\n\nBiggest family (96.9% of all html) is fully model-driven at 100%; the remaining\n3.1% (the shell family) is 100% at the scaffolding level with the center pane\ntied to the already-verified envelope family and only the west pane left as a\nper-theory opaque fragment. 100% was not required this round; it was achieved for\nbyte-parity, with the west-pane generation noted as the single remaining modeling\ngap.\n\n## Artifacts\n\n* `examples/corpus_html.rs` — the bulk harness (crate example).\n* `tests/fixtures/html_sample.ndjson` + `html_page_generality_sample_byte_\n  identical` — committed permanent regression (20 bodies, 6 theories).\n* `workspace/scratch/` — the jq extractor, `center_linkage.py`,\n  `proof_mismatch.py` (regenerable analyses; the 620 MB `html_corpus.ndjson`\n  extract is transient and can be rebuilt with the jq loop above).\n","numLines":181,"startLine":1,"totalLines":181}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"218a3309-d31c-4941-9f02-e700f644bdc8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
