{"parentUuid":"84426afe-e405-492b-823a-37f21216e7ae","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Cd7dtVjx7xmk2E4x8WH57","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The round-2 web src edits are proofscript.rs (12:19), envelope.rs (12:23), lib.rs (12:23), plus the harness/fixtures/test. Let me read those and the round-1 report to establish the baseline."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1039,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cd7dtTznQWZzdgLgaNh1i","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"a1f2ecc4-e83b-4e2a-8643-e7f8d78299f8","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:07.595Z","effort":"xhigh","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"a1f2ecc4-e83b-4e2a-8643-e7f8d78299f8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Cd7dtVjx7xmk2E4x8WH57","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XZ8kSvWZKDwWV5dtTjJmv2","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/examples/corpus_html.rs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1039,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cd7dtTznQWZzdgLgaNh1i","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"0cc01bec-d21a-498e-b5f5-ac9551642f36","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:08.596Z","effort":"xhigh","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"0cc01bec-d21a-498e-b5f5-ac9551642f36","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"2961bd88-c930-4506-bcca-f9d40cc278bf","agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XZ8kSvWZKDwWV5dtTjJmv2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t//! Corpus-wide byte-parity harness for the two HTML page families.\n2\t//!\n3\t//! Reads an NDJSON extract of every `kind == \"html\"` response body across all\n4\t//! captured crawl manifests (one JSON object per line, produced by the jq\n5\t//! extractor documented in `workspace/REPORT2.md`), renders each body from the\n6\t//! crate's own templates using inputs taken from *observable* sources, and\n7\t//! reports per-family byte-exact reproduction counts.\n8\t//!\n9\t//! Run: `cargo run --release --example corpus_html -- <html_corpus.ndjson>`\n10\t//!\n11\t//! Each input record is `{mf, name, ver, file, u, b}`:\n12\t//! * `mf`   — manifest id (for diagnostics only)\n13\t//! * `name` — theory name, taken once per manifest from that manifest's\n14\t//!   `overview/help` `<title>` (a sibling artifact, not this body)\n15\t//! * `ver`  — Tamarin version, likewise from `overview/help`\n16\t//! * `file` — source filename, likewise from `overview/help`\n17\t//! * `u`    — the request URL key (index normalised to `#` by the capture tool)\n18\t//! * `b`    — the captured response body we must reproduce\n19\t//!\n20\t//! Non-circularity: for the `intdot` family the only value read back from the\n21\t//! target body `b` is the scalar request index (the `#` the capture erased); the\n22\t//! theory name comes from a sibling page and the path tail comes from the URL\n23\t//! key, so a byte match proves the template, name placement and tail-passthrough\n24\t//! independently. For the `overview` family the west/center pane inner HTML are\n25\t//! treated as opaque fragments (prover/proof-state output) exactly as the\n26\t//! committed page tests do; the harness measures whether the crate's shell\n27\t//! scaffolding + slot substitution reproduces the surrounding page bytes.\n28\t\n29\tuse std::collections::BTreeMap;\n30\tuse std::io::{BufRead, BufReader};\n31\t\n32\tuse serde::Deserialize;\n33\tuse web_clean::intdot::{dotsrc_path, render_intdot};\n34\tuse web_clean::page::{render_page, PageParams};\n35\t\n36\t#[derive(Deserialize)]\n37\tstruct Rec {\n38\t    #[allow(dead_code)]\n39\t    mf: String,\n40\t    name: String,\n41\t    ver: String,\n42\t    file: String,\n43\t    u: String,\n44\t    b: String,\n45\t}\n46\t\n47\t/// Split `/thy/trace/#/<handler>/<tail>` into (handler, tail).\n48\tfn handler_and_tail(u: &str) -> Option<(&str, &str)> {\n49\t    let rest = u.strip_prefix(\"/thy/trace/#/\")?;\n50\t    match rest.split_once('/') {\n51\t        Some((h, t)) => Some((h, t)),\n52\t        None => Some((rest, \"\")),\n53\t    }\n54\t}\n55\t\n56\t/// Read the decimal index that follows `needle` in `body` (e.g. the request\n57\t/// index the capture tool normalised to `#`, recovered from an emitted link).\n58\tfn index_after(body: &str, needle: &str) -> Option<u64> {\n59\t    let start = body.find(needle)? + needle.len();\n60\t    let digits: String = body[start..].chars().take_while(|c| c.is_ascii_digit()).collect();\n61\t    digits.parse().ok()\n62\t}\n63\t\n64\t/// Extract the substring of `body` strictly between `open` and the next `close`\n65\t/// occurring after it.\n66\tfn between<'a>(body: &'a str, open: &str, close: &str) -> Option<&'a str> {\n67\t    let a = body.find(open)? + open.len();\n68\t    let b = body[a..].find(close)? + a;\n69\t    Some(&body[a..b])\n70\t}\n71\t\n72\t// Fixed pane delimiters (observed; the same bytes the page shell uses).\n73\tconst WEST_OPEN: &str = r#\"<div class=\"monospace\" id=\"proof\">\"#;\n74\tconst WEST_CLOSE: &str = r#\"</div></div></div><div class=\"ui-layout-east\">\"#;\n75\tconst CENTER_OPEN: &str = r#\"<div id=\"ui-main-display\">\"#;\n76\tconst CENTER_CLOSE: &str = r#\"</div></div></div><div id=\"dialog\">\"#;\n77\t\n78\t#[derive(Default)]\n79\tstruct Tally {\n80\t    total: usize,\n81\t    ok: usize,\n82\t    /// example failing URL (first seen)\n83\t    first_fail: Option<String>,\n84\t}\n85\timpl Tally {\n86\t    fn record(&mut self, ok: bool, u: &str) {\n87\t        self.total += 1;\n88\t        if ok {\n89\t            self.ok += 1;\n90\t        } else if self.first_fail.is_none() {\n91\t            self.first_fail = Some(u.to_string());\n92\t        }\n93\t    }\n94\t    fn pct(&self) -> f64 {\n95\t        if self.total == 0 {\n96\t            0.0\n97\t        } else {\n98\t            100.0 * self.ok as f64 / self.total as f64\n99\t        }\n100\t    }\n101\t}\n102\t\n103\tfn overview_subfamily(tail: &str) -> &'static str {\n104\t    if tail == \"help\" {\n105\t        \"overview/help\"\n106\t    } else if tail.starts_with(\"proof/\") {\n107\t        \"overview/proof\"\n108\t    } else {\n109\t        \"overview/other\"\n110\t    }\n111\t}\n112\t\n113\tfn main() {\n114\t    let path = std::env::args().nth(1).expect(\"usage: corpus_html <ndjson>\");\n115\t    let f = std::fs::File::open(&path).expect(\"open corpus\");\n116\t    let reader = BufReader::new(f);\n117\t\n118\t    let mut intdot = Tally::default();\n119\t    let mut intdot_name_guard_fail = 0usize;\n120\t    let mut intdot_tail_guard_fail = 0usize;\n121\t    let mut overview: BTreeMap<&'static str, Tally> = BTreeMap::new();\n122\t    // center-pane linkage sub-metric: does the center pane end in the observed\n123\t    // single trailing space that distinguishes it from the raw main/* html?\n124\t    let mut center_trailing_space = Tally::default();\n125\t    let mut other_handler: BTreeMap<String, usize> = BTreeMap::new();\n126\t    let mut parse_errors = 0usize;\n127\t\n128\t    for line in reader.lines() {\n129\t        let line = line.expect(\"read line\");\n130\t        if line.trim().is_empty() {\n131\t            continue;\n132\t        }\n133\t        let r: Rec = match serde_json::from_str(&line) {\n134\t            Ok(r) => r,\n135\t            Err(_) => {\n136\t                parse_errors += 1;\n137\t                continue;\n138\t            }\n139\t        };\n140\t        let Some((handler, tail)) = handler_and_tail(&r.u) else {\n141\t            *other_handler.entry(r.u.clone()).or_default() += 1;\n142\t            continue;\n143\t        };\n144\t\n145\t        match handler {\n146\t            \"intdot\" => {\n147\t                // idx: the one value read from the target (the erased request index).\n148\t                let idx = match index_after(&r.b, \"dotsrc=\\\"/thy/trace/\") {\n149\t                    Some(i) => i,\n150\t                    None => {\n151\t                        intdot.record(false, &r.u);\n152\t                        continue;\n153\t                    }\n154\t                };\n155\t                // Non-circularity guards (independent of the byte compare):\n156\t                //  - the name shown in the body matches the sibling-derived name\n157\t                //  - the path tail echoed in dotsrc matches the URL key tail\n158\t                if let Some(bn) = between(&r.b, \"<title>Theory: \", \"</title>\") {\n159\t                    if bn != r.name {\n160\t                        intdot_name_guard_fail += 1;\n161\t                    }\n162\t                }\n163\t                if let Some(bt) = between(&r.b, \"interactive-graph-def/\", \"\\\"\") {\n164\t                    if bt != tail {\n165\t                        intdot_tail_guard_fail += 1;\n166\t                    }\n167\t                }\n168\t                let dotsrc = dotsrc_path(idx, tail);\n169\t                let got = render_intdot(&r.name, &dotsrc);\n170\t                intdot.record(got == r.b, &r.u);\n171\t            }\n172\t            \"overview\" => {\n173\t                let sub = overview_subfamily(tail);\n174\t                let idx = match index_after(&r.b, \"action=\\\"/thy/trace/\") {\n175\t                    Some(i) => i,\n176\t                    None => {\n177\t                        overview.entry(sub).or_default().record(false, &r.u);\n178\t                        continue;\n179\t                    }\n180\t                };\n181\t                let west = between(&r.b, WEST_OPEN, WEST_CLOSE);\n182\t                let center = between(&r.b, CENTER_OPEN, CENTER_CLOSE);\n183\t                let (west, center) = match (west, center) {\n184\t                    (Some(w), Some(c)) => (w, c),\n185\t                    _ => {\n186\t                        overview.entry(sub).or_default().record(false, &r.u);\n187\t                        continue;\n188\t                    }\n189\t                };\n190\t                let params = PageParams {\n191\t                    theory_name: &r.name,\n192\t                    index: idx,\n193\t                    version: &r.ver,\n194\t                    filename: &r.file,\n195\t                };\n196\t                let got = render_page(&params, west, center);\n197\t                overview.entry(sub).or_default().record(got == r.b, &r.u);\n198\t                center_trailing_space.record(center.ends_with(' '), &r.u);\n199\t            }\n200\t            _ => {\n201\t                *other_handler.entry(handler.to_string()).or_default() += 1;\n202\t            }\n203\t        }\n204\t    }\n205\t\n206\t    println!(\"== HTML corpus byte-parity ==\");\n207\t    println!(\"input parse errors: {parse_errors}\");\n208\t    println!();\n209\t    println!(\n210\t        \"intdot           : {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%   (first fail: {:?})\",\n211\t        intdot.ok,\n212\t        intdot.total,\n213\t        intdot.pct(),\n214\t        intdot.first_fail\n215\t    );\n216\t    println!(\n217\t        \"  name guard fails: {intdot_name_guard_fail}   tail guard fails: {intdot_tail_guard_fail} (both must be 0)\"\n218\t    );\n219\t    let mut ov_ok = 0;\n220\t    let mut ov_total = 0;\n221\t    for (sub, t) in &overview {\n222\t        ov_ok += t.ok;\n223\t        ov_total += t.total;\n224\t        println!(\n225\t            \"{sub:<17}: {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%   (first fail: {:?})\",\n226\t            t.ok,\n227\t            t.total,\n228\t            t.pct(),\n229\t            t.first_fail\n230\t        );\n231\t    }\n232\t    println!(\n233\t        \"overview (all)   : {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%\",\n234\t        ov_ok,\n235\t        ov_total,\n236\t        if ov_total == 0 { 0.0 } else { 100.0 * ov_ok as f64 / ov_total as f64 }\n237\t    );\n238\t    println!(\n239\t        \"  center-pane trailing-space rule holds: {}/{} = {:.2}%\",\n240\t        center_trailing_space.ok,\n241\t        center_trailing_space.total,\n242\t        center_trailing_space.pct()\n243\t    );\n244\t    if !other_handler.is_empty() {\n245\t        println!(\"\\nunexpected handlers (should be none):\");\n246\t        for (h, n) in &other_handler {\n247\t            println!(\"  {h}: {n}\");\n248\t        }\n249\t    }\n250\t    let grand_ok = intdot.ok + ov_ok;\n251\t    let grand_total = intdot.total + ov_total;\n252\t    println!(\n253\t        \"\\nALL html         : {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%\",\n254\t        grand_ok,\n255\t        grand_total,\n256\t        if grand_total == 0 { 0.0 } else { 100.0 * grand_ok as f64 / grand_total as f64 }\n257\t    );\n258\t}\n259\t"}]},"uuid":"1183d3df-a86d-4c01-a998-bc7b204f72cb","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:08.609Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/examples/corpus_html.rs","content":"//! Corpus-wide byte-parity harness for the two HTML page families.\n//!\n//! Reads an NDJSON extract of every `kind == \"html\"` response body across all\n//! captured crawl manifests (one JSON object per line, produced by the jq\n//! extractor documented in `workspace/REPORT2.md`), renders each body from the\n//! crate's own templates using inputs taken from *observable* sources, and\n//! reports per-family byte-exact reproduction counts.\n//!\n//! Run: `cargo run --release --example corpus_html -- <html_corpus.ndjson>`\n//!\n//! Each input record is `{mf, name, ver, file, u, b}`:\n//! * `mf`   — manifest id (for diagnostics only)\n//! * `name` — theory name, taken once per manifest from that manifest's\n//!   `overview/help` `<title>` (a sibling artifact, not this body)\n//! * `ver`  — Tamarin version, likewise from `overview/help`\n//! * `file` — source filename, likewise from `overview/help`\n//! * `u`    — the request URL key (index normalised to `#` by the capture tool)\n//! * `b`    — the captured response body we must reproduce\n//!\n//! Non-circularity: for the `intdot` family the only value read back from the\n//! target body `b` is the scalar request index (the `#` the capture erased); the\n//! theory name comes from a sibling page and the path tail comes from the URL\n//! key, so a byte match proves the template, name placement and tail-passthrough\n//! independently. For the `overview` family the west/center pane inner HTML are\n//! treated as opaque fragments (prover/proof-state output) exactly as the\n//! committed page tests do; the harness measures whether the crate's shell\n//! scaffolding + slot substitution reproduces the surrounding page bytes.\n\nuse std::collections::BTreeMap;\nuse std::io::{BufRead, BufReader};\n\nuse serde::Deserialize;\nuse web_clean::intdot::{dotsrc_path, render_intdot};\nuse web_clean::page::{render_page, PageParams};\n\n#[derive(Deserialize)]\nstruct Rec {\n    #[allow(dead_code)]\n    mf: String,\n    name: String,\n    ver: String,\n    file: String,\n    u: String,\n    b: String,\n}\n\n/// Split `/thy/trace/#/<handler>/<tail>` into (handler, tail).\nfn handler_and_tail(u: &str) -> Option<(&str, &str)> {\n    let rest = u.strip_prefix(\"/thy/trace/#/\")?;\n    match rest.split_once('/') {\n        Some((h, t)) => Some((h, t)),\n        None => Some((rest, \"\")),\n    }\n}\n\n/// Read the decimal index that follows `needle` in `body` (e.g. the request\n/// index the capture tool normalised to `#`, recovered from an emitted link).\nfn index_after(body: &str, needle: &str) -> Option<u64> {\n    let start = body.find(needle)? + needle.len();\n    let digits: String = body[start..].chars().take_while(|c| c.is_ascii_digit()).collect();\n    digits.parse().ok()\n}\n\n/// Extract the substring of `body` strictly between `open` and the next `close`\n/// occurring after it.\nfn between<'a>(body: &'a str, open: &str, close: &str) -> Option<&'a str> {\n    let a = body.find(open)? + open.len();\n    let b = body[a..].find(close)? + a;\n    Some(&body[a..b])\n}\n\n// Fixed pane delimiters (observed; the same bytes the page shell uses).\nconst WEST_OPEN: &str = r#\"<div class=\"monospace\" id=\"proof\">\"#;\nconst WEST_CLOSE: &str = r#\"</div></div></div><div class=\"ui-layout-east\">\"#;\nconst CENTER_OPEN: &str = r#\"<div id=\"ui-main-display\">\"#;\nconst CENTER_CLOSE: &str = r#\"</div></div></div><div id=\"dialog\">\"#;\n\n#[derive(Default)]\nstruct Tally {\n    total: usize,\n    ok: usize,\n    /// example failing URL (first seen)\n    first_fail: Option<String>,\n}\nimpl Tally {\n    fn record(&mut self, ok: bool, u: &str) {\n        self.total += 1;\n        if ok {\n            self.ok += 1;\n        } else if self.first_fail.is_none() {\n            self.first_fail = Some(u.to_string());\n        }\n    }\n    fn pct(&self) -> f64 {\n        if self.total == 0 {\n            0.0\n        } else {\n            100.0 * self.ok as f64 / self.total as f64\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn overview_subfamily(tail: &str) -> &'static str {\n    if tail == \"help\" {\n        \"overview/help\"\n    } else if tail.starts_with(\"proof/\") {\n        \"overview/proof\"\n    } else {\n        \"overview/other\"\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let path = std::env::args().nth(1).expect(\"usage: corpus_html <ndjson>\");\n    let f = std::fs::File::open(&path).expect(\"open corpus\");\n    let reader = BufReader::new(f);\n\n    let mut intdot = Tally::default();\n    let mut intdot_name_guard_fail = 0usize;\n    let mut intdot_tail_guard_fail = 0usize;\n    let mut overview: BTreeMap<&'static str, Tally> = BTreeMap::new();\n    // center-pane linkage sub-metric: does the center pane end in the observed\n    // single trailing space that distinguishes it from the raw main/* html?\n    let mut center_trailing_space = Tally::default();\n    let mut other_handler: BTreeMap<String, usize> = BTreeMap::new();\n    let mut parse_errors = 0usize;\n\n    for line in reader.lines() {\n        let line = line.expect(\"read line\");\n        if line.trim().is_empty() {\n            continue;\n        }\n        let r: Rec = match serde_json::from_str(&line) {\n            Ok(r) => r,\n            Err(_) => {\n                parse_errors += 1;\n                continue;\n            }\n        };\n        let Some((handler, tail)) = handler_and_tail(&r.u) else {\n            *other_handler.entry(r.u.clone()).or_default() += 1;\n            continue;\n        };\n\n        match handler {\n            \"intdot\" => {\n                // idx: the one value read from the target (the erased request index).\n                let idx = match index_after(&r.b, \"dotsrc=\\\"/thy/trace/\") {\n                    Some(i) => i,\n                    None => {\n                        intdot.record(false, &r.u);\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                };\n                // Non-circularity guards (independent of the byte compare):\n                //  - the name shown in the body matches the sibling-derived name\n                //  - the path tail echoed in dotsrc matches the URL key tail\n                if let Some(bn) = between(&r.b, \"<title>Theory: \", \"</title>\") {\n                    if bn != r.name {\n                        intdot_name_guard_fail += 1;\n                    }\n                }\n                if let Some(bt) = between(&r.b, \"interactive-graph-def/\", \"\\\"\") {\n                    if bt != tail {\n                        intdot_tail_guard_fail += 1;\n                    }\n                }\n                let dotsrc = dotsrc_path(idx, tail);\n                let got = render_intdot(&r.name, &dotsrc);\n                intdot.record(got == r.b, &r.u);\n            }\n            \"overview\" => {\n                let sub = overview_subfamily(tail);\n                let idx = match index_after(&r.b, \"action=\\\"/thy/trace/\") {\n                    Some(i) => i,\n                    None => {\n                        overview.entry(sub).or_default().record(false, &r.u);\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                };\n                let west = between(&r.b, WEST_OPEN, WEST_CLOSE);\n                let center = between(&r.b, CENTER_OPEN, CENTER_CLOSE);\n                let (west, center) = match (west, center) {\n                    (Some(w), Some(c)) => (w, c),\n                    _ => {\n                        overview.entry(sub).or_default().record(false, &r.u);\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                };\n                let params = PageParams {\n                    theory_name: &r.name,\n                    index: idx,\n                    version: &r.ver,\n                    filename: &r.file,\n                };\n                let got = render_page(&params, west, center);\n                overview.entry(sub).or_default().record(got == r.b, &r.u);\n                center_trailing_space.record(center.ends_with(' '), &r.u);\n            }\n            _ => {\n                *other_handler.entry(handler.to_string()).or_default() += 1;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    println!(\"== HTML corpus byte-parity ==\");\n    println!(\"input parse errors: {parse_errors}\");\n    println!();\n    println!(\n        \"intdot           : {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%   (first fail: {:?})\",\n        intdot.ok,\n        intdot.total,\n        intdot.pct(),\n        intdot.first_fail\n    );\n    println!(\n        \"  name guard fails: {intdot_name_guard_fail}   tail guard fails: {intdot_tail_guard_fail} (both must be 0)\"\n    );\n    let mut ov_ok = 0;\n    let mut ov_total = 0;\n    for (sub, t) in &overview {\n        ov_ok += t.ok;\n        ov_total += t.total;\n        println!(\n            \"{sub:<17}: {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%   (first fail: {:?})\",\n            t.ok,\n            t.total,\n            t.pct(),\n            t.first_fail\n        );\n    }\n    println!(\n        \"overview (all)   : {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%\",\n        ov_ok,\n        ov_total,\n        if ov_total == 0 { 0.0 } else { 100.0 * ov_ok as f64 / ov_total as f64 }\n    );\n    println!(\n        \"  center-pane trailing-space rule holds: {}/{} = {:.2}%\",\n        center_trailing_space.ok,\n        center_trailing_space.total,\n        center_trailing_space.pct()\n    );\n    if !other_handler.is_empty() {\n        println!(\"\\nunexpected handlers (should be none):\");\n        for (h, n) in &other_handler {\n            println!(\"  {h}: {n}\");\n        }\n    }\n    let grand_ok = intdot.ok + ov_ok;\n    let grand_total = intdot.total + ov_total;\n    println!(\n        \"\\nALL html         : {:>6}/{:<6} = {:6.2}%\",\n        grand_ok,\n        grand_total,\n        if grand_total == 0 { 0.0 } else { 100.0 * grand_ok as f64 / grand_total as f64 }\n    );\n}\n","numLines":259,"startLine":1,"totalLines":259}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0cc01bec-d21a-498e-b5f5-ac9551642f36","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"1183d3df-a86d-4c01-a998-bc7b204f72cb","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Cd7dtVjx7xmk2E4x8WH57","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ARrdi7FiWwzoTFnGSyaGW9","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/src/proofscript.rs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1039,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cd7dtTznQWZzdgLgaNh1i","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"3a21fa63-c7dc-400d-bcf3-d9d9b95b392e","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:09.438Z","effort":"xhigh","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"3a21fa63-c7dc-400d-bcf3-d9d9b95b392e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"2961bd88-c930-4506-bcca-f9d40cc278bf","agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ARrdi7FiWwzoTFnGSyaGW9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t//! The proof-script (west) pane markup embedded in the theory-view page and in\n2\t//! the `main/*` navigation.\n3\t//!\n4\t//! ## Line model (observed)\n5\t//! The pane is a flat sequence of logical lines. Rendering emits each line's\n6\t//! text followed by the literal `\"<br/>\\n\"`, and finally a single trailing\n7\t//! space `\" \"`. A blank line is an element whose text is empty (yielding a lone\n8\t//! `\"<br/>\\n\"`). This one rule reproduces the exact blank-line spacing of both\n9\t//! the no-lemma and multi-lemma captures.\n10\t//!\n11\t//! ## Element order\n12\t//! 1. `theory NAME begin` header line\n13\t//! 2. one blank + link line per theory item, in order: Message theory, rules,\n14\t//!    Tactic(s), Raw sources, Refined sources\n15\t//! 3. one blank + the `add lemma` link for position `<first>`\n16\t//! 4. for each lemma: one blank, the lemma's body lines, one blank, the lemma's\n17\t//!    trailing `add lemma` link (targeting that lemma's name)\n18\t//! 5. one blank + `end`\n19\t//!\n20\t//! When there are zero lemmas, step 4 contributes nothing, which leaves TWO\n21\t//! blank lines between the `<first>` add-link and `end` (matching the capture).\n22\t//!\n23\t//! ## Slots that come from the prover (opaque here)\n24\t//! The lemma declaration HTML (`decl_html`: the pretty-printed `lemma NAME:` +\n25\t//! quantifier + formula, already entity-escaped and wrapped in `hl_operator`\n26\t//! spans), the rules label/count, the sources descriptions, and — for a solved\n27\t//! proof — each proof step's method HTML and case names. Everything else (the\n28\t//! anchors, keywords, indentation, links) is generated here.\n29\t//!\n30\t//! ## Indices\n31\t//! Every internal href uses the resolved numeric theory index, never `#`.\n32\t\n33\t/// A theory item shown as a top link in the proof-script pane.\n34\tpub enum Item<'a> {\n35\t    /// `Message theory` link.\n36\t    Message,\n37\t    /// Multiset rewriting rules link. `label` is the prover's wording\n38\t    /// (`\"Multiset rewriting rules\"`, or with `\" and restrictions\"`), `count`\n39\t    /// the rule count.\n40\t    Rules { label: &'a str, count: usize },\n41\t    /// `Tactic(s)` link.\n42\t    Tactic,\n43\t    /// `Raw sources` link; `desc` e.g. `\"4 cases, deconstructions complete\"`.\n44\t    RawSources { desc: &'a str },\n45\t    /// `Refined sources` link; note the label carries a trailing space.\n46\t    RefinedSources { desc: &'a str },\n47\t}\n48\t\n49\t/// How a lemma's proof is displayed.\n50\tpub enum Proof<'a> {\n51\t    /// Unproven: a single `by sorry` proof-step line. The declaration and the\n52\t    /// edit/delete line are emitted bare (no status wrapper).\n53\t    Sorry,\n54\t    /// A solved/partial proof rendered as an explicit list of proof lines.\n55\t    ///\n56\t    /// Observed: when a lemma carries a proof, the whole lemma header — the\n57\t    /// declaration HTML plus the following edit/delete line — is wrapped in a\n58\t    /// single `<span class=\"{status}\">…</span>` reflecting the lemma's overall\n59\t    /// proof status (`hl_good` for the proved lemmas in the corpus). The wrapper\n60\t    /// opens immediately before the declaration and closes right after the\n61\t    /// delete-lemma anchor (spanning the intervening `<br/>` line breaks).\n62\t    Steps {\n63\t        /// Lemma-level status class carried by the header wrapper span.\n64\t        status: &'a str,\n65\t        /// The rendered proof-tree lines, in document order.\n66\t        lines: Vec<ProofLine<'a>>,\n67\t    },\n68\t}\n69\t\n70\t/// One line of a rendered proof tree.\n71\tpub enum ProofLine<'a> {\n72\t    /// A proof-method step (an applied method or a leaf such as `SOLVED`).\n73\t    Step {\n74\t        depth: usize,\n75\t        /// Status class, e.g. `\"hl_good\"`.\n76\t        status: &'a str,\n77\t        /// Full href, e.g. `/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec/_/B_2`.\n78\t        href: String,\n79\t        /// Prover method HTML, e.g. `<span class=\"hl_keyword\">simplify</span>`.\n80\t        method_html: &'a str,\n81\t        /// Annotation shown in the remove-step anchor (usually empty).\n82\t        annotation: &'a str,\n83\t        /// Whether the line is prefixed with a wrapped `by ` keyword.\n84\t        by: bool,\n85\t    },\n86\t    /// A `case NAME` header.\n87\t    Case {\n88\t        depth: usize,\n89\t        status: &'a str,\n90\t        name: &'a str,\n91\t    },\n92\t    /// A `next` separator between sibling cases.\n93\t    Next { depth: usize, status: &'a str },\n94\t    /// A `qed` closing a case block.\n95\t    Qed { depth: usize, status: &'a str },\n96\t}\n97\t\n98\t/// A single lemma block.\n99\tpub struct Lemma<'a> {\n100\t    /// Lemma name (used in the edit/delete/add/proof links).\n101\t    pub name: &'a str,\n102\t    /// Opaque prover-produced declaration HTML (`lemma NAME:` + formula).\n103\t    pub decl_html: &'a str,\n104\t    /// Proof display.\n105\t    pub proof: Proof<'a>,\n106\t}\n107\t\n108\t/// The whole proof-script pane input.\n109\tpub struct Overview<'a> {\n110\t    pub theory_name: &'a str,\n111\t    pub index: u64,\n112\t    pub items: Vec<Item<'a>>,\n113\t    pub lemmas: Vec<Lemma<'a>>,\n114\t}\n115\t\n116\tfn indent(depth: usize) -> String {\n117\t    \"&nbsp;&nbsp;\".repeat(depth)\n118\t}\n119\t\n120\t/// Render one proof-tree line (public so the line grammar can be unit-tested).\n121\tpub fn render_proof_line(line: &ProofLine) -> String {\n122\t    match line {\n123\t        ProofLine::Step {\n124\t            depth,\n125\t            status,\n126\t            href,\n127\t            method_html,\n128\t            annotation,\n129\t            by,\n130\t        } => {\n131\t            let ind = indent(*depth);\n132\t            let by_prefix = if *by {\n133\t                format!(r#\"<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">by</span> </span>\"#)\n134\t            } else {\n135\t                String::new()\n136\t            };\n137\t            format!(\n138\t                r#\"{ind}{by_prefix}<a class=\"internal-link proof-step {status}\" href=\"{href}\">{method_html}</a><a class=\"internal-link remove-step\" href=\"{href}\">{annotation}</a>\"#\n139\t            )\n140\t        }\n141\t        ProofLine::Case {\n142\t            depth,\n143\t            status,\n144\t            name,\n145\t        } => format!(\n146\t            r#\"{}<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">case</span> {name}</span>\"#,\n147\t            indent(*depth)\n148\t        ),\n149\t        ProofLine::Next { depth, status } => format!(\n150\t            r#\"{}<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">next</span></span>\"#,\n151\t            indent(*depth)\n152\t        ),\n153\t        ProofLine::Qed { depth, status } => format!(\n154\t            r#\"{}<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">qed</span></span>\"#,\n155\t            indent(*depth)\n156\t        ),\n157\t    }\n158\t}\n159\t\n160\tfn item_line(item: &Item, idx: u64) -> String {\n161\t    match item {\n162\t        Item::Message => format!(\n163\t            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/message\"><strong>Message theory</strong> </a>\"#\n164\t        ),\n165\t        Item::Rules { label, count } => format!(\n166\t            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/rules\"><strong>{label}</strong> ({count})</a>\"#\n167\t        ),\n168\t        Item::Tactic => format!(\n169\t            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/tactic\"><strong>Tactic(s)</strong> </a>\"#\n170\t        ),\n171\t        Item::RawSources { desc } => format!(\n172\t            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/cases/raw/0/0\"><strong>Raw sources</strong> ({desc})</a>\"#\n173\t        ),\n174\t        Item::RefinedSources { desc } => format!(\n175\t            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/cases/refined/0/0\"><strong>Refined sources </strong> ({desc})</a>\"#\n176\t        ),\n177\t    }\n178\t}\n179\t\n180\tfn add_link(idx: u64, target: &str) -> String {\n181\t    format!(r#\"<a class=\"internal-link add\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/add/{target}\">add lemma</a>\"#)\n182\t}\n183\t\n184\tfn edit_delete_line(idx: u64, name: &str) -> String {\n185\t    format!(\n186\t        r#\"<a class=\"internal-link edit\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/edit/{name}\">edit lemma</a>  or  <a class=\"internal-link delete\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/delete/{name}\">delete lemma</a>\"#\n187\t    )\n188\t}\n189\t\n190\tfn sorry_line(idx: u64, name: &str) -> String {\n191\t    format!(\n192\t        r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">by</span> <a class=\"internal-link proof-step sorry-step\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/proof/{name}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">sorry</span></a>\"#\n193\t    )\n194\t}\n195\t\n196\t/// The theory header line: `theory NAME begin`.\n197\tfn header_line(name: &str, idx: u64) -> String {\n198\t    format!(\n199\t        r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">theory</span> <a class=\"internal-link help\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/help\">{name}</a> <span class=\"hl_keyword\">begin</span>\"#\n200\t    )\n201\t}\n202\t\n203\t/// Render the full inner HTML of the `#proof` west pane.\n204\tpub fn render_proof_script(o: &Overview) -> String {\n205\t    let idx = o.index;\n206\t    // Build the flat element list.\n207\t    let mut elems: Vec<String> = Vec::new();\n208\t    elems.push(header_line(o.theory_name, idx));\n209\t    for item in &o.items {\n210\t        elems.push(String::new());\n211\t        elems.push(item_line(item, idx));\n212\t    }\n213\t    elems.push(String::new());\n214\t    elems.push(add_link(idx, \"%3Cfirst%3E\"));\n215\t    if o.lemmas.is_empty() {\n216\t        elems.push(String::new());\n217\t        elems.push(String::new());\n218\t    } else {\n219\t        for lemma in &o.lemmas {\n220\t            elems.push(String::new());\n221\t            match &lemma.proof {\n222\t                Proof::Sorry => {\n223\t                    // Bare declaration, edit/delete line, then a single `by sorry`.\n224\t                    elems.push(lemma.decl_html.to_string());\n225\t                    elems.push(edit_delete_line(idx, lemma.name));\n226\t                    elems.push(sorry_line(idx, lemma.name));\n227\t                }\n228\t                Proof::Steps { status, lines } => {\n229\t                    // The header (declaration + edit/delete line) is wrapped in a\n230\t                    // status span that opens before the declaration and closes\n231\t                    // after the delete anchor; the proof lines follow unwrapped.\n232\t                    elems.push(format!(r#\"<span class=\"{status}\">{}\"#, lemma.decl_html));\n233\t                    elems.push(format!(\"{}</span>\", edit_delete_line(idx, lemma.name)));\n234\t                    for l in lines {\n235\t                        elems.push(render_proof_line(l));\n236\t                    }\n237\t                }\n238\t            }\n239\t            elems.push(String::new());\n240\t            elems.push(add_link(idx, lemma.name));\n241\t        }\n242\t        elems.push(String::new());\n243\t    }\n244\t    elems.push(header_end());\n245\t\n246\t    let mut out = String::new();\n247\t    for e in &elems {\n248\t        out.push_str(e);\n249\t        out.push_str(\"<br/>\\n\");\n250\t    }\n251\t    out.push(' ');\n252\t    out\n253\t}\n254\t\n255\tfn header_end() -> String {\n256\t    r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">end</span>\"#.to_string()\n257\t}\n258\t\n259\t#[cfg(test)]\n260\tmod tests {\n261\t    use super::*;\n262\t\n263\t    #[test]\n264\t    fn proof_step_simplify_line() {\n265\t        let l = ProofLine::Step {\n266\t            depth: 0,\n267\t            status: \"hl_good\",\n268\t            href: \"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec\".to_string(),\n269\t            method_html: r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">simplify</span>\"#,\n270\t            annotation: \"\",\n271\t            by: false,\n272\t        };\n273\t        assert_eq!(\n274\t            render_proof_line(&l),\n275\t            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link proof-step hl_good\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">simplify</span></a><a class=\"internal-link remove-step\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec\"></a>\"#\n276\t        );\n277\t    }\n278\t\n279\t    #[test]\n280\t    fn case_header_indented() {\n281\t        let l = ProofLine::Case {\n282\t            depth: 1,\n283\t            status: \"hl_good\",\n284\t            name: \"B_2\",\n285\t        };\n286\t        assert_eq!(\n287\t            render_proof_line(&l),\n288\t            r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">case</span> B_2</span>\"#\n289\t        );\n290\t    }\n291\t\n292\t    #[test]\n293\t    fn by_step_contradiction() {\n294\t        let l = ProofLine::Step {\n295\t            depth: 4,\n296\t            status: \"hl_good\",\n297\t            href: \"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/unforgeability/_/B_2/S_1/B_1/case_1/B_2\".to_string(),\n298\t            method_html: r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">contradiction</span> <span class=\"hl_comment\">/* cyclic */</span>\"#,\n299\t            annotation: \"\",\n300\t            by: true,\n301\t        };\n302\t        let expected = r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">by</span> </span><a class=\"internal-link proof-step hl_good\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/unforgeability/_/B_2/S_1/B_1/case_1/B_2\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">contradiction</span> <span class=\"hl_comment\">/* cyclic */</span></a><a class=\"internal-link remove-step\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/unforgeability/_/B_2/S_1/B_1/case_1/B_2\"></a>\"#;\n303\t        assert_eq!(render_proof_line(&l), expected);\n304\t    }\n305\t\n306\t    #[test]\n307\t    fn qed_and_next() {\n308\t        assert_eq!(\n309\t            render_proof_line(&ProofLine::Qed { depth: 1, status: \"hl_good\" }),\n310\t            r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">qed</span></span>\"#\n311\t        );\n312\t        assert_eq!(\n313\t            render_proof_line(&ProofLine::Next { depth: 3, status: \"hl_good\" }),\n314\t            r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">next</span></span>\"#\n315\t        );\n316\t    }\n317\t}\n318\t"}]},"uuid":"f0a98722-d651-4e34-824d-4217ddcad8a3","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:09.446Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/src/proofscript.rs","content":"//! The proof-script (west) pane markup embedded in the theory-view page and in\n//! the `main/*` navigation.\n//!\n//! ## Line model (observed)\n//! The pane is a flat sequence of logical lines. Rendering emits each line's\n//! text followed by the literal `\"<br/>\\n\"`, and finally a single trailing\n//! space `\" \"`. A blank line is an element whose text is empty (yielding a lone\n//! `\"<br/>\\n\"`). This one rule reproduces the exact blank-line spacing of both\n//! the no-lemma and multi-lemma captures.\n//!\n//! ## Element order\n//! 1. `theory NAME begin` header line\n//! 2. one blank + link line per theory item, in order: Message theory, rules,\n//!    Tactic(s), Raw sources, Refined sources\n//! 3. one blank + the `add lemma` link for position `<first>`\n//! 4. for each lemma: one blank, the lemma's body lines, one blank, the lemma's\n//!    trailing `add lemma` link (targeting that lemma's name)\n//! 5. one blank + `end`\n//!\n//! When there are zero lemmas, step 4 contributes nothing, which leaves TWO\n//! blank lines between the `<first>` add-link and `end` (matching the capture).\n//!\n//! ## Slots that come from the prover (opaque here)\n//! The lemma declaration HTML (`decl_html`: the pretty-printed `lemma NAME:` +\n//! quantifier + formula, already entity-escaped and wrapped in `hl_operator`\n//! spans), the rules label/count, the sources descriptions, and — for a solved\n//! proof — each proof step's method HTML and case names. Everything else (the\n//! anchors, keywords, indentation, links) is generated here.\n//!\n//! ## Indices\n//! Every internal href uses the resolved numeric theory index, never `#`.\n\n/// A theory item shown as a top link in the proof-script pane.\npub enum Item<'a> {\n    /// `Message theory` link.\n    Message,\n    /// Multiset rewriting rules link. `label` is the prover's wording\n    /// (`\"Multiset rewriting rules\"`, or with `\" and restrictions\"`), `count`\n    /// the rule count.\n    Rules { label: &'a str, count: usize },\n    /// `Tactic(s)` link.\n    Tactic,\n    /// `Raw sources` link; `desc` e.g. `\"4 cases, deconstructions complete\"`.\n    RawSources { desc: &'a str },\n    /// `Refined sources` link; note the label carries a trailing space.\n    RefinedSources { desc: &'a str },\n}\n\n/// How a lemma's proof is displayed.\npub enum Proof<'a> {\n    /// Unproven: a single `by sorry` proof-step line. The declaration and the\n    /// edit/delete line are emitted bare (no status wrapper).\n    Sorry,\n    /// A solved/partial proof rendered as an explicit list of proof lines.\n    ///\n    /// Observed: when a lemma carries a proof, the whole lemma header — the\n    /// declaration HTML plus the following edit/delete line — is wrapped in a\n    /// single `<span class=\"{status}\">…</span>` reflecting the lemma's overall\n    /// proof status (`hl_good` for the proved lemmas in the corpus). The wrapper\n    /// opens immediately before the declaration and closes right after the\n    /// delete-lemma anchor (spanning the intervening `<br/>` line breaks).\n    Steps {\n        /// Lemma-level status class carried by the header wrapper span.\n        status: &'a str,\n        /// The rendered proof-tree lines, in document order.\n        lines: Vec<ProofLine<'a>>,\n    },\n}\n\n/// One line of a rendered proof tree.\npub enum ProofLine<'a> {\n    /// A proof-method step (an applied method or a leaf such as `SOLVED`).\n    Step {\n        depth: usize,\n        /// Status class, e.g. `\"hl_good\"`.\n        status: &'a str,\n        /// Full href, e.g. `/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec/_/B_2`.\n        href: String,\n        /// Prover method HTML, e.g. `<span class=\"hl_keyword\">simplify</span>`.\n        method_html: &'a str,\n        /// Annotation shown in the remove-step anchor (usually empty).\n        annotation: &'a str,\n        /// Whether the line is prefixed with a wrapped `by ` keyword.\n        by: bool,\n    },\n    /// A `case NAME` header.\n    Case {\n        depth: usize,\n        status: &'a str,\n        name: &'a str,\n    },\n    /// A `next` separator between sibling cases.\n    Next { depth: usize, status: &'a str },\n    /// A `qed` closing a case block.\n    Qed { depth: usize, status: &'a str },\n}\n\n/// A single lemma block.\npub struct Lemma<'a> {\n    /// Lemma name (used in the edit/delete/add/proof links).\n    pub name: &'a str,\n    /// Opaque prover-produced declaration HTML (`lemma NAME:` + formula).\n    pub decl_html: &'a str,\n    /// Proof display.\n    pub proof: Proof<'a>,\n}\n\n/// The whole proof-script pane input.\npub struct Overview<'a> {\n    pub theory_name: &'a str,\n    pub index: u64,\n    pub items: Vec<Item<'a>>,\n    pub lemmas: Vec<Lemma<'a>>,\n}\n\nfn indent(depth: usize) -> String {\n    \"&nbsp;&nbsp;\".repeat(depth)\n}\n\n/// Render one proof-tree line (public so the line grammar can be unit-tested).\npub fn render_proof_line(line: &ProofLine) -> String {\n    match line {\n        ProofLine::Step {\n            depth,\n            status,\n            href,\n            method_html,\n            annotation,\n            by,\n        } => {\n            let ind = indent(*depth);\n            let by_prefix = if *by {\n                format!(r#\"<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">by</span> </span>\"#)\n            } else {\n                String::new()\n            };\n            format!(\n                r#\"{ind}{by_prefix}<a class=\"internal-link proof-step {status}\" href=\"{href}\">{method_html}</a><a class=\"internal-link remove-step\" href=\"{href}\">{annotation}</a>\"#\n            )\n        }\n        ProofLine::Case {\n            depth,\n            status,\n            name,\n        } => format!(\n            r#\"{}<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">case</span> {name}</span>\"#,\n            indent(*depth)\n        ),\n        ProofLine::Next { depth, status } => format!(\n            r#\"{}<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">next</span></span>\"#,\n            indent(*depth)\n        ),\n        ProofLine::Qed { depth, status } => format!(\n            r#\"{}<span class=\"{status}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">qed</span></span>\"#,\n            indent(*depth)\n        ),\n    }\n}\n\nfn item_line(item: &Item, idx: u64) -> String {\n    match item {\n        Item::Message => format!(\n            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/message\"><strong>Message theory</strong> </a>\"#\n        ),\n        Item::Rules { label, count } => format!(\n            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/rules\"><strong>{label}</strong> ({count})</a>\"#\n        ),\n        Item::Tactic => format!(\n            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/tactic\"><strong>Tactic(s)</strong> </a>\"#\n        ),\n        Item::RawSources { desc } => format!(\n            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/cases/raw/0/0\"><strong>Raw sources</strong> ({desc})</a>\"#\n        ),\n        Item::RefinedSources { desc } => format!(\n            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/cases/refined/0/0\"><strong>Refined sources </strong> ({desc})</a>\"#\n        ),\n    }\n}\n\nfn add_link(idx: u64, target: &str) -> String {\n    format!(r#\"<a class=\"internal-link add\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/add/{target}\">add lemma</a>\"#)\n}\n\nfn edit_delete_line(idx: u64, name: &str) -> String {\n    format!(\n        r#\"<a class=\"internal-link edit\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/edit/{name}\">edit lemma</a>  or  <a class=\"internal-link delete\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/delete/{name}\">delete lemma</a>\"#\n    )\n}\n\nfn sorry_line(idx: u64, name: &str) -> String {\n    format!(\n        r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">by</span> <a class=\"internal-link proof-step sorry-step\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/proof/{name}\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">sorry</span></a>\"#\n    )\n}\n\n/// The theory header line: `theory NAME begin`.\nfn header_line(name: &str, idx: u64) -> String {\n    format!(\n        r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">theory</span> <a class=\"internal-link help\" href=\"/thy/trace/{idx}/main/help\">{name}</a> <span class=\"hl_keyword\">begin</span>\"#\n    )\n}\n\n/// Render the full inner HTML of the `#proof` west pane.\npub fn render_proof_script(o: &Overview) -> String {\n    let idx = o.index;\n    // Build the flat element list.\n    let mut elems: Vec<String> = Vec::new();\n    elems.push(header_line(o.theory_name, idx));\n    for item in &o.items {\n        elems.push(String::new());\n        elems.push(item_line(item, idx));\n    }\n    elems.push(String::new());\n    elems.push(add_link(idx, \"%3Cfirst%3E\"));\n    if o.lemmas.is_empty() {\n        elems.push(String::new());\n        elems.push(String::new());\n    } else {\n        for lemma in &o.lemmas {\n            elems.push(String::new());\n            match &lemma.proof {\n                Proof::Sorry => {\n                    // Bare declaration, edit/delete line, then a single `by sorry`.\n                    elems.push(lemma.decl_html.to_string());\n                    elems.push(edit_delete_line(idx, lemma.name));\n                    elems.push(sorry_line(idx, lemma.name));\n                }\n                Proof::Steps { status, lines } => {\n                    // The header (declaration + edit/delete line) is wrapped in a\n                    // status span that opens before the declaration and closes\n                    // after the delete anchor; the proof lines follow unwrapped.\n                    elems.push(format!(r#\"<span class=\"{status}\">{}\"#, lemma.decl_html));\n                    elems.push(format!(\"{}</span>\", edit_delete_line(idx, lemma.name)));\n                    for l in lines {\n                        elems.push(render_proof_line(l));\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            elems.push(String::new());\n            elems.push(add_link(idx, lemma.name));\n        }\n        elems.push(String::new());\n    }\n    elems.push(header_end());\n\n    let mut out = String::new();\n    for e in &elems {\n        out.push_str(e);\n        out.push_str(\"<br/>\\n\");\n    }\n    out.push(' ');\n    out\n}\n\nfn header_end() -> String {\n    r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">end</span>\"#.to_string()\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn proof_step_simplify_line() {\n        let l = ProofLine::Step {\n            depth: 0,\n            status: \"hl_good\",\n            href: \"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec\".to_string(),\n            method_html: r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">simplify</span>\"#,\n            annotation: \"\",\n            by: false,\n        };\n        assert_eq!(\n            render_proof_line(&l),\n            r#\"<a class=\"internal-link proof-step hl_good\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">simplify</span></a><a class=\"internal-link remove-step\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/exec\"></a>\"#\n        );\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn case_header_indented() {\n        let l = ProofLine::Case {\n            depth: 1,\n            status: \"hl_good\",\n            name: \"B_2\",\n        };\n        assert_eq!(\n            render_proof_line(&l),\n            r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">case</span> B_2</span>\"#\n        );\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn by_step_contradiction() {\n        let l = ProofLine::Step {\n            depth: 4,\n            status: \"hl_good\",\n            href: \"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/unforgeability/_/B_2/S_1/B_1/case_1/B_2\".to_string(),\n            method_html: r#\"<span class=\"hl_keyword\">contradiction</span> <span class=\"hl_comment\">/* cyclic */</span>\"#,\n            annotation: \"\",\n            by: true,\n        };\n        let expected = r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">by</span> </span><a class=\"internal-link proof-step hl_good\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/unforgeability/_/B_2/S_1/B_1/case_1/B_2\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">contradiction</span> <span class=\"hl_comment\">/* cyclic */</span></a><a class=\"internal-link remove-step\" href=\"/thy/trace/3/main/proof/unforgeability/_/B_2/S_1/B_1/case_1/B_2\"></a>\"#;\n        assert_eq!(render_proof_line(&l), expected);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn qed_and_next() {\n        assert_eq!(\n            render_proof_line(&ProofLine::Qed { depth: 1, status: \"hl_good\" }),\n            r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">qed</span></span>\"#\n        );\n        assert_eq!(\n            render_proof_line(&ProofLine::Next { depth: 3, status: \"hl_good\" }),\n            r#\"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"hl_good\"><span class=\"hl_keyword\">next</span></span>\"#\n        );\n    }\n}\n","numLines":318,"startLine":1,"totalLines":318}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3a21fa63-c7dc-400d-bcf3-d9d9b95b392e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"f0a98722-d651-4e34-824d-4217ddcad8a3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Cd7dtVjx7xmk2E4x8WH57","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SjVVMR31xkYBoTSVAFw4ow","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/src/envelope.rs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1039,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cd7dtTznQWZzdgLgaNh1i","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"27effbcc-f49a-479a-b5df-43e360cd9216","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:10.097Z","effort":"xhigh","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"27effbcc-f49a-479a-b5df-43e360cd9216","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"2961bd88-c930-4506-bcca-f9d40cc278bf","agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SjVVMR31xkYBoTSVAFw4ow","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t//! JSON response envelopes for the `main/*` (and `method/*`, `autoprove/*`)\n2\t//! AJAX handlers.\n3\t//!\n4\t//! Observed: every `kind=json` response body is one of exactly two compact\n5\t//! JSON objects, with keys in this order and no insignificant whitespace:\n6\t//!   * content:  `{\"html\":<string>,\"title\":<string>}`\n7\t//!   * redirect: `{\"redirect\":<string>}`\n8\t//!\n9\t//! There is no trailing newline. Non-ASCII is emitted as literal UTF-8 (no\n10\t//! `\\uXXXX`), and `/ < > &` are NOT backslash/entity escaped inside the JSON\n11\t//! string — i.e. standard JSON string escaping (only `\" \\` and control chars).\n12\t//! `serde_json`'s default serialization reproduces this exactly.\n13\t\n14\tuse serde::Serialize;\n15\t\n16\t/// A content pane response: rendered HTML plus the pane title.\n17\t#[derive(Serialize)]\n18\tpub struct Content<'a> {\n19\t    pub html: &'a str,\n20\t    pub title: &'a str,\n21\t}\n22\t\n23\t/// A redirect response instructing the client to navigate to `redirect`.\n24\t#[derive(Serialize)]\n25\tpub struct Redirect<'a> {\n26\t    pub redirect: &'a str,\n27\t}\n28\t\n29\t/// Serialize `{\"html\":..,\"title\":..}` exactly as the web layer does.\n30\tpub fn render_content(html: &str, title: &str) -> String {\n31\t    serde_json::to_string(&Content { html, title }).expect(\"Content serializes\")\n32\t}\n33\t\n34\t/// Serialize `{\"redirect\":..}` exactly as the web layer does.\n35\tpub fn render_redirect(path: &str) -> String {\n36\t    serde_json::to_string(&Redirect { redirect: path }).expect(\"Redirect serializes\")\n37\t}\n38\t\n39\t#[cfg(test)]\n40\tmod tests {\n41\t    use super::*;\n42\t\n43\t    #[test]\n44\t    fn content_envelope_shape() {\n45\t        assert_eq!(\n46\t            render_content(\"this is a mistake<br/>\\n\", \"Lemma: exec\"),\n47\t            r#\"{\"html\":\"this is a mistake<br/>\\n\",\"title\":\"Lemma: exec\"}\"#\n48\t        );\n49\t    }\n50\t\n51\t    #[test]\n52\t    fn redirect_envelope_shape() {\n53\t        assert_eq!(\n54\t            render_redirect(\"/thy/trace/4/overview/proof/exec/_\"),\n55\t            r#\"{\"redirect\":\"/thy/trace/4/overview/proof/exec/_\"}\"#\n56\t        );\n57\t    }\n58\t\n59\t    #[test]\n60\t    fn keeps_literal_utf8_and_unescaped_angle_brackets() {\n61\t        let s = render_content(\"<span>∃</span>\", \"t\");\n62\t        assert!(s.contains(\"<span>∃</span>\"), \"got {s}\");\n63\t        assert!(!s.contains(\"\\\\u\"), \"should not \\\\u-escape: {s}\");\n64\t    }\n65\t}\n66\t"}]},"uuid":"b8147cd7-0616-42a4-bc1e-59b6986fb022","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:10.108Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/web-clean/src/envelope.rs","content":"//! JSON response envelopes for the `main/*` (and `method/*`, `autoprove/*`)\n//! AJAX handlers.\n//!\n//! Observed: every `kind=json` response body is one of exactly two compact\n//! JSON objects, with keys in this order and no insignificant whitespace:\n//!   * content:  `{\"html\":<string>,\"title\":<string>}`\n//!   * redirect: `{\"redirect\":<string>}`\n//!\n//! There is no trailing newline. Non-ASCII is emitted as literal UTF-8 (no\n//! `\\uXXXX`), and `/ < > &` are NOT backslash/entity escaped inside the JSON\n//! string — i.e. standard JSON string escaping (only `\" \\` and control chars).\n//! `serde_json`'s default serialization reproduces this exactly.\n\nuse serde::Serialize;\n\n/// A content pane response: rendered HTML plus the pane title.\n#[derive(Serialize)]\npub struct Content<'a> {\n    pub html: &'a str,\n    pub title: &'a str,\n}\n\n/// A redirect response instructing the client to navigate to `redirect`.\n#[derive(Serialize)]\npub struct Redirect<'a> {\n    pub redirect: &'a str,\n}\n\n/// Serialize `{\"html\":..,\"title\":..}` exactly as the web layer does.\npub fn render_content(html: &str, title: &str) -> String {\n    serde_json::to_string(&Content { html, title }).expect(\"Content serializes\")\n}\n\n/// Serialize `{\"redirect\":..}` exactly as the web layer does.\npub fn render_redirect(path: &str) -> String {\n    serde_json::to_string(&Redirect { redirect: path }).expect(\"Redirect serializes\")\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn content_envelope_shape() {\n        assert_eq!(\n            render_content(\"this is a mistake<br/>\\n\", \"Lemma: exec\"),\n            r#\"{\"html\":\"this is a mistake<br/>\\n\",\"title\":\"Lemma: exec\"}\"#\n        );\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn redirect_envelope_shape() {\n        assert_eq!(\n            render_redirect(\"/thy/trace/4/overview/proof/exec/_\"),\n            r#\"{\"redirect\":\"/thy/trace/4/overview/proof/exec/_\"}\"#\n        );\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn keeps_literal_utf8_and_unescaped_angle_brackets() {\n        let s = render_content(\"<span>∃</span>\", \"t\");\n        assert!(s.contains(\"<span>∃</span>\"), \"got {s}\");\n        assert!(!s.contains(\"\\\\u\"), \"should not \\\\u-escape: {s}\");\n    }\n}\n","numLines":66,"startLine":1,"totalLines":66}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"27effbcc-f49a-479a-b5df-43e360cd9216","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"b8147cd7-0616-42a4-bc1e-59b6986fb022","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Cd7dtVjx7xmk2E4x8WH57","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01J3fua2nYAufH9AtBsZ7Pb3","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/REPORT.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"output_tokens":1760,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1039},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1760,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1039,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cd7dtTznQWZzdgLgaNh1i","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"dca20cf5-015e-447f-95e5-58e4e83a2259","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:10.289Z","effort":"xhigh","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"dca20cf5-015e-447f-95e5-58e4e83a2259","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"2961bd88-c930-4506-bcca-f9d40cc278bf","agentId":"ac1b65c4df499573b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J3fua2nYAufH9AtBsZ7Pb3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# REPORT.md — clean-room web layer (`web-clean`)\n2\t\n3\tFinal report for the `weblayer` cluster. Everything below was derived from\n4\tblack-box observation only: the 81 pre-captured crawl manifests in\n5\t`oracle/captured_responses/` (captured program OUTPUT) and live probing of the\n6\tsanctioned oracle binary (`QUERIES.log` [L0]–[L6]). No file under\n7\t`/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/` was read; the only tamarin-rs touch was EXECUTING\n8\tthe sanctioned oracle binary for live probing.\n9\t\n10\t## Components (crate `web-clean`, std + serde/serde_json only)\n11\t\n12\t| module | LOC | responsibility |\n13\t|--------|----:|----------------|\n14\t| `route.rs` | 217 | parse `/thy/<kind>/<index>/<handler>/<args…>` into a structured route (descriptive grammar; not a dispatcher) |\n15\t| `envelope.rs` | 65 | the two JSON response shapes `{\"html\",\"title\"}` / `{\"redirect\"}` (compact, fixed key order, no trailing newline) |\n16\t| `escape.rs` | 54 | HTML entity escaping (`& < > \" '` → 5 entities; UTF-8 pass-through) |\n17\t| `page.rs` + `shell_template.rs` | 59 | full theory-view HTML shell (`overview/*`), 4 slots: NAME/IDX/VERSION/FILENAME |\n18\t| `proofscript.rs` | 317 | proof-script (west) pane: header, item links, add/edit/delete links, `by sorry`, and the solved proof-tree line grammar (step/case/next/qed/by, indentation, status wrapper) |\n19\t| `forms.rs` | 119 | edit / delete / add-lemma form bodies |\n20\t| `intdot.rs` | 55 | `intdot` mini-page + empty-graph DOT skeleton |\n21\t| `errors.rs` + `notfound_template.rs` | 37 | 404 Not Found page |\n22\t| `text.rs` | 47 | plain-text bodies (`source`/`message`, `next`/`prev`) + proof URL builder |\n23\t| `lib.rs` | 35 | module map / crate docs |\n24\t| **src total** | **1005** | |\n25\t| `tests/parity.rs` | 334 | byte-parity tests against captured fixtures |\n26\t\n27\tByte-exact scaffolding copied from observed oracle output (compatibility\n28\tcontent) lives in `shell_template.rs` and `notfound_template.rs`.\n29\t\n30\t## Tests\n31\t\n32\t`cargo test` → **37 passing, 0 failing** (19 unit + 18 integration/parity),\n33\t`cargo clippy` clean.\n34\t\n35\tParity coverage (byte-identical against captured/observed output):\n36\t- JSON envelopes: **2450 distinct bodies** deduped across all 81 manifests\n37\t  (1583 content + 867 redirect), plus every body of the Chaum and issue515\n38\t  manifests. Reproduced byte-for-byte by `serde_json` default serialization.\n39\t- Full theory-view page: 3 pages — `overview/help` for two theories, and\n40\t  `overview/proof/exec` (a proof view at version 3, a distinct page type/index).\n41\t- Proof-script west pane: unproven (0-lemma issue515, 2-lemma Chaum) **and** a\n42\t  fully solved 2-lemma proof tree (40 proof lines with branching cases,\n43\t  `next` separators, `qed` nesting to depth 5, and by-prefixed final steps).\n44\t- Forms (edit/delete/add, incl. `<first>` percent/entity encoding), intdot\n45\t  mini-page, empty DOT, 404 page, source/next text pass-through.\n46\t- Unit tests: route grammar, escaping, envelope shapes, proof-line grammar.\n47\t\n48\tThe solved-tree test feeds the crate's own observation model\n49\t(`proof_lines_{exec,unforgeability}.json`) and the crate's URL builder through\n50\t`render_proof_script`, asserting the whole west pane byte-for-byte; only the\n51\tproof-method HTML and case names are treated as opaque prover fragments.\n52\t\n53\tLive probe [L6] independently corroborated the model on a *fresh* theory\n54\t(NSLPK3): index page, `overview/help` (version 1.13.0), `next`/`prev` text\n55\ttargets, the `autoprove` redirect with its index bump (1→2), the `main/proof`\n56\t`{html,title}` envelope with `&#39;` escaping, a redirect JSON with no trailing\n57\tnewline, `%23` index → 404, and an empty DOT that is **byte-identical** (`cmp`)\n58\tto the committed fixture from a different theory.\n59\t\n60\t## Oracle query count\n61\t\n62\tQUERIES.log records **29** logged interactions: 23 manifest-exploration steps\n63\t([001]–[023], source A) + 6 live-server steps ([L0]–[L6], one a tooling-bug\n64\tfinding, source B). The `hs_server.sh --port` parsing bug ([L0]) was worked\n65\taround with a local wrapper (`scratchpad/wl_server.sh`, `--port=<n>` form).\n66\t\n67\t## Work done this (continuation) session\n68\t\n69\t1. Verified the inherited crate builds and all inherited parity tests actually\n70\t   execute and pass (the reported \"0 tests\" was stale — fixtures were already\n71\t   wired; confirmed 35 → now 37).\n72\t2. Enumerated the authoritative handler/kind census over all 48 824 dynamic\n73\t   routes and folded it into BEHAVIOR §1 (autoprove/next/prev/overview shapes).\n74\t3. Found and reproduced the **solved proof tree** (the named coverage gap):\n75\t   discovered the proven-lemma header wrapper (`<span class=\"hl_good\">…</span>`\n76\t   spanning decl + edit/delete line), refined the `Proof` model accordingly,\n77\t   parsed the two Chaum proofs into a JSON observation model, and added two\n78\t   new byte-parity tests (solved west pane + proof-view page).\n79\t4. Live-corroborated the route/envelope model on a fresh theory; fixed clippy.\n80\t5. Extended BEHAVIOR.md (§1 census, §6 proved-header wrapper, §11 coverage) and\n81\t   QUERIES.log; wrote this report.\n82\t\n83\t## Gaps / notes (for the similarity audit + later integration)\n84\t\n85\t- **Prover fragments, by design out of scope**: pretty-printed signatures,\n86\t  rules, lemma formulas, constraint systems / \"Applicable Proof Methods\" center\n87\t  bodies, proof-method HTML, case names, source cases, non-empty DOT graphs,\n88\t  wf-warning text, and the theory `source` string. The crate reproduces the\n89\t  web-layer scaffolding *around* these and takes them as opaque inputs.\n90\t- **Not byte-tested (non-deterministic)**: the index page rows (load timestamp,\n91\t  temp origin path) and the source footer (compile time, git rev, Maude\n92\t  version). Structure documented in BEHAVIOR §7/§10; template not asserted.\n93\t- **Unobserved, hence unimplemented**: the `diff` theory-kind (only `trace`\n94\t  appears); proof-status classes other than `hl_good` / `sorry-step`\n95\t  (`hl_bad`/`hl_dead` are plausible for falsified/dead but never captured);\n96\t  the `POST` upload/reload/append/download bodies (seen only as emitted link\n97\t  targets). `render_proof_line` accepts an arbitrary status string, so\n98\t  falsified/dead colors need only a caller supplying the class — no code change.\n99\t- **Integration**: render functions take an explicit input model (version index,\n100\t  version string, filename, timestamps, and all prover fragments), so a caller\n101\t  supplying the observed values reproduces the observed bytes. Adapters mapping\n102\t  the workspace's internal types onto this model are a later (dirty-room) step.\n103\t"}]},"uuid":"8cf5f325-4fa3-45f0-86f7-d99d3ec20d6a","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:34:10.299Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/weblayer/workspace/REPORT.md","content":"# REPORT.md — clean-room web layer (`web-clean`)\n\nFinal report for the `weblayer` cluster. Everything below was derived from\nblack-box observation only: the 81 pre-captured crawl manifests in\n`oracle/captured_responses/` (captured program OUTPUT) and live probing of the\nsanctioned oracle binary (`QUERIES.log` [L0]–[L6]). No file under\n`/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/` was read; the only tamarin-rs touch was EXECUTING\nthe sanctioned oracle binary for live probing.\n\n## Components (crate `web-clean`, std + serde/serde_json only)\n\n| module | LOC | responsibility |\n|--------|----:|----------------|\n| `route.rs` | 217 | parse `/thy/<kind>/<index>/<handler>/<args…>` into a structured route (descriptive grammar; not a dispatcher) |\n| `envelope.rs` | 65 | the two JSON response shapes `{\"html\",\"title\"}` / `{\"redirect\"}` (compact, fixed key order, no trailing newline) |\n| `escape.rs` | 54 | HTML entity escaping (`& < > \" '` → 5 entities; UTF-8 pass-through) |\n| `page.rs` + `shell_template.rs` | 59 | full theory-view HTML shell (`overview/*`), 4 slots: NAME/IDX/VERSION/FILENAME |\n| `proofscript.rs` | 317 | proof-script (west) pane: header, item links, add/edit/delete links, `by sorry`, and the solved proof-tree line grammar (step/case/next/qed/by, indentation, status wrapper) |\n| `forms.rs` | 119 | edit / delete / add-lemma form bodies |\n| `intdot.rs` | 55 | `intdot` mini-page + empty-graph DOT skeleton |\n| `errors.rs` + `notfound_template.rs` | 37 | 404 Not Found page |\n| `text.rs` | 47 | plain-text bodies (`source`/`message`, `next`/`prev`) + proof URL builder |\n| `lib.rs` | 35 | module map / crate docs |\n| **src total** | **1005** | |\n| `tests/parity.rs` | 334 | byte-parity tests against captured fixtures |\n\nByte-exact scaffolding copied from observed oracle output (compatibility\ncontent) lives in `shell_template.rs` and `notfound_template.rs`.\n\n## Tests\n\n`cargo test` → **37 passing, 0 failing** (19 unit + 18 integration/parity),\n`cargo clippy` clean.\n\nParity coverage (byte-identical against captured/observed output):\n- JSON envelopes: **2450 distinct bodies** deduped across all 81 manifests\n  (1583 content + 867 redirect), plus every body of the Chaum and issue515\n  manifests. Reproduced byte-for-byte by `serde_json` default serialization.\n- Full theory-view page: 3 pages — `overview/help` for two theories, and\n  `overview/proof/exec` (a proof view at version 3, a distinct page type/index).\n- Proof-script west pane: unproven (0-lemma issue515, 2-lemma Chaum) **and** a\n  fully solved 2-lemma proof tree (40 proof lines with branching cases,\n  `next` separators, `qed` nesting to depth 5, and by-prefixed final steps).\n- Forms (edit/delete/add, incl. `<first>` percent/entity encoding), intdot\n  mini-page, empty DOT, 404 page, source/next text pass-through.\n- Unit tests: route grammar, escaping, envelope shapes, proof-line grammar.\n\nThe solved-tree test feeds the crate's own observation model\n(`proof_lines_{exec,unforgeability}.json`) and the crate's URL builder through\n`render_proof_script`, asserting the whole west pane byte-for-byte; only the\nproof-method HTML and case names are treated as opaque prover fragments.\n\nLive probe [L6] independently corroborated the model on a *fresh* theory\n(NSLPK3): index page, `overview/help` (version 1.13.0), `next`/`prev` text\ntargets, the `autoprove` redirect with its index bump (1→2), the `main/proof`\n`{html,title}` envelope with `&#39;` escaping, a redirect JSON with no trailing\nnewline, `%23` index → 404, and an empty DOT that is **byte-identical** (`cmp`)\nto the committed fixture from a different theory.\n\n## Oracle query count\n\nQUERIES.log records **29** logged interactions: 23 manifest-exploration steps\n([001]–[023], source A) + 6 live-server steps ([L0]–[L6], one a tooling-bug\nfinding, source B). The `hs_server.sh --port` parsing bug ([L0]) was worked\naround with a local wrapper (`scratchpad/wl_server.sh`, `--port=<n>` form).\n\n## Work done this (continuation) session\n\n1. Verified the inherited crate builds and all inherited parity tests actually\n   execute and pass (the reported \"0 tests\" was stale — fixtures were already\n   wired; confirmed 35 → now 37).\n2. Enumerated the authoritative handler/kind census over all 48 824 dynamic\n   routes and folded it into BEHAVIOR §1 (autoprove/next/prev/overview shapes).\n3. Found and reproduced the **solved proof tree** (the named coverage gap):\n   discovered the proven-lemma header wrapper (`<span class=\"hl_good\">…</span>`\n   spanning decl + edit/delete line), refined the `Proof` model accordingly,\n   parsed the two Chaum proofs into a JSON observation model, and added two\n   new byte-parity tests (solved west pane + proof-view page).\n4. Live-corroborated the route/envelope model on a fresh theory; fixed clippy.\n5. Extended BEHAVIOR.md (§1 census, §6 proved-header wrapper, §11 coverage) and\n   QUERIES.log; wrote this report.\n\n## Gaps / notes (for the similarity audit + later integration)\n\n- **Prover fragments, by design out of scope**: pretty-printed signatures,\n  rules, lemma formulas, constraint systems / \"Applicable Proof Methods\" center\n  bodies, proof-method HTML, case names, source cases, non-empty DOT graphs,\n  wf-warning text, and the theory `source` string. The crate reproduces the\n  web-layer scaffolding *around* these and takes them as opaque inputs.\n- **Not byte-tested (non-deterministic)**: the index page rows (load timestamp,\n  temp origin path) and the source footer (compile time, git rev, Maude\n  version). Structure documented in BEHAVIOR §7/§10; template not asserted.\n- **Unobserved, hence unimplemented**: the `diff` theory-kind (only `trace`\n  appears); proof-status classes other than `hl_good` / `sorry-step`\n  (`hl_bad`/`hl_dead` are plausible for falsified/dead but never captured);\n  the `POST` upload/reload/append/download bodies (seen only as emitted link\n  targets). `render_proof_line` accepts an arbitrary status string, so\n  falsified/dead colors need only a caller supplying the class — no code change.\n- **Integration**: render functions take an explicit input model (version index,\n  version string, filename, timestamps, and all prover fragments), so a caller\n  supplying the observed values reproduces the observed bytes. Adapters mapping\n  the workspace's internal types onto this model are a later (dirty-room) step.\n","numLines":103,"startLine":1,"totalLines":103}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"dca20cf5-015e-447f-95e5-58e4e83a2259","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
